23 employee continues at the same rate until the employee is paid or for 30 days,
24 whichever is less, if the employer fails to pay the wages or compensation, as
25 applicable: (1) for an employee who is discharged, within 3 days after the wages or
26 compensation of the employee becomes due; (2) for an employee who is placed on
27 nonworking status, within 3 days after the wages of the employee becomes due;
28 and (3) for an employee who resigns or quits, on the day the wages or
29 compensation is due. (NRS 608.040)
30 Section 3 revises the amount of such a penalty. Rather than providing that the
31 wages or compensation of the employee continues at the same rate until paid or for
32 30 days, whichever is less, section 3 requires an employer who fails to pay the
33 wages of an employee who has resigned, quit or been discharged or placed on
34 nonworking status within the required time to pay the employee an additional
35 amount equal to the amount the employee would receive for 8 hours of work at the
36 rate of 1 1/2 times his or her hourly wage rate for each day or portion of a day that
37 the wages to which the employee is entitled and any additional amount required by
38 section 3, are not paid or for 30 days, whichever is less.
39 Section 3 additionally requires such an employer to pay to an employee who
40 has resigned, quit or been discharged an amount equal to the amount of
41 compensation the employee would have earned for each day or portion of a day that
42 the wages to which the employee is entitled and any additional amount required by
43 section 3 are not paid or for 30 days, whichever is less. Section 3 requires that
44 amount to be paid in the same manner and on the same day on which the employee
45 would have regularly been paid compensation if the employee had earned
46 compensation during that period.
